The second DAIS Learnathon is held at CSBD (MPI-CBG) in Dresden from June 4th to June 8th, 2018.

= Preparation =
<ol>
  <li>Follow the Gitter channel for news: https://gitter.im/juglab/DaisLearnathon18</li>
  <li>Bring your laptop</li>
  <li>Make sure, you have the following stuff installed:
    <ul>
      <li>Eclipse (Oxygen) or IntelliJ</li>
      <li>GIT</li>
      <li>Maven</li>
      <li>bash or zsh</li>
      <li>Miniconda or Anaconda
        <ul>
          <li>Install [https://conda.io/miniconda.html Miniconda] if you do not have installed it or Anaconda already. (We need the version for Python 3!)</li>
          <li>Your <code>.bashrc</code> or <code>.zshrc</code> will need a line like this: <code>export PATH="/Users/someforders/miniconda3/bin:$PATH"</code></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
There will be a software installation session on Sunday evening (June 4th).
There we can help you to get the software installed and running.
